### Component 2: Node.js Backend (`/backend`)

The server that bridges the web platform and the mobile app.

#### [NEW] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/TinasheHando/Documents/Eastern%20Sojourner/backend/server.js)
- Express.js REST API server
- **Endpoints**:
  - `POST /api/nonce` — Generate a cryptographic nonce (with QRNG placeholder), store in memory with TTL, return `{ nonceId, nonce, expiresAt }`
  - `POST /api/verify` — Accept `{ nonceId, userId, signature, publicKey, gps, timestamp }`, verify ECDSA signature covers entire payload, **burn nonce after one use** (replay protection), return `{ verified: true/false }`
  - `GET /api/verify-status/:nonceId` — Check if a nonce has been verified (for web polling)
  - `POST /api/sos` — Accept SOS incident report `{ userId, type, gps, timestamp, message }`, log and broadcast
  - `GET /api/geofences` — Return geo-fence zone definitions (polygons + risk levels)
- All endpoints return clean JSON (Burp Suite-ready)
- CORS enabled for local development

#### [NEW] [crypto-utils.js](file:///c:/Users/TinasheHando/Documents/Eastern%20Sojourner/backend/crypto-utils.js)
- `generateNonce()` — Uses `crypto.randomBytes(32)` with **QRNG placeholder comment** documenting how to swap in quantum random source
- `verifySignature(payload, signature, publicKey)` — ECDSA P-256 verification
- **PQC placeholder**: Documented architecture for ML-DSA (CRYSTALS-Dilithium) signature verification when `liboqs` or NIST PQC libraries become Node-ready
- Nonce store with automatic TTL expiration

#### [NEW] [package.json](file:///c:/Users/TinasheHando/Documents/Eastern%20Sojourner/backend/package.json)
- Dependencies: `express`, `cors`, `uuid`, `elliptic` (ECDSA)

